REFACTOR_GOVERNANCE_RULES

Status: Mandatory (Blocking)
Scope: renderer/main modular refactor waves, naming passes, skill workflow updates

DEFAULT_AGENT

- polyglot-default-director-agent

DEFAULT_SKILL_STACK

1) polyglot-default-orchestrator
2) linked-naming-governor
3) pre-assign-naming-gate
4) json-instruction-registry-governor
5) strict-format-cleanup
6) dictionary-alias-sync
7) polyglot-quality-benchmark-gate
8) refactor-blocking-gate

DEFAULT_POLYGLOT_FLOW

1) pseudo-blueprint-planner stage (english + pseudocode blueprint)
2) unified-two-pass-wrapper stage preflight (identify args + execute pipeline smoke)
3) language-fit-selector stage (weighted scoring + candidate set)
4) pseudocode-polyglot-translator stage (per-language function mapping)
5) optimization/fix loop per language
6) polyglot-quality-benchmark-gate stage (strict tests/security/SxS benchmarks)
7) final primary/fallback language recommendation by measured effectiveness

RUN_HIERARCHY_ORDER (RUN FIRST)

1) context intake and snapshot load
2) stage planning (create vs maintain)
3) wrapper preflight stage (two-pass argument + execution validation)
4) blueprint stage (full create or incremental growth)
5) language selection stage
6) translation stage
7) checks/security/benchmark gates (as planned)
8) recommendation + context save

CONTINUE_TRIGGER_RULE

- User intent `continue` or `general workflow` maps to the default runner:
  - `npm run workflow:general -- ...`
- Deterministic behavior:
  1) run full planning flow (`create` if no context, otherwise `maintain`)
  2) run stage agents via polyglot pipeline
  3) run data-separation scan for object/name/group constants
  4) publish artifacts and updated context
- Explicit maintain shortcut:
  - `npm run workflow:continue -- ...`

CREATE_VS_MAINTAIN_RULE

- Create command:
  - `npm run polyglot:create -- ...`
  - Must generate full baseline blueprint + pseudocode.
- Maintain command:
  - `npm run polyglot:maintain -- ...`
  - Must reuse existing blueprint/pseudocode and grow incrementally by default.
  - Full pseudocode regeneration only with `--force-pseudocode`.
- Required persisted context files:
  - `data/output/databases/polyglot-default/context/run_state.json`
  - `data/output/databases/polyglot-default/plan/hierarchy_order.md`
  - `data/output/databases/polyglot-default/analysis/wrapper_preflight_report.json`

DIRECT_DISPATCH_RULE

- Director dispatches directly to stage agents by default.
- Skip manager layers unless both are true:
  - selected languages > 6
  - target platforms > 3

AGENT_ACCESS_CONTROL_RULE

- Source of truth ID: `source://agent_access_control` (resolved dynamically by `scripts/project-source-resolver.js`)
- Every agent must declare role, `controls_cap`, `allowed_controls`, `startup_tools`, and `startup_tool_cap`.
- Startup tools are the only tools allowed without escalation.
- If an agent needs any tool outside `startup_tools`, it must submit a request before using the tool:
  - `npm run agent:request-access -- --agent-id <agent-id> --requested-tool <tool-id> --privilege-flag <flag-id> --reason "<why-needed>"`
- Required request fields:
  - `agent_id`
  - `requested_tool`
  - `privilege_flag`
  - `reason`
- Request logs are mandatory and append-only:
  - `source://request_log_file`
- Default policy is deny-by-default for non-startup tools until a reviewer approves the request.

AGENT_REGISTRY_ALIGNMENT_RULE

- Agent metadata must stay synchronized across:
  - `to-do/agents/*.yaml`
  - `to-do/agents/agents_registry.yaml`
  - `to-do/agents/agent_access_control.json`
  - `to-do/skills/agent_workflows.json`
- Any pass that edits agents/skills/rules metadata must run:
  - `npm run agents:validate`
- `workflow:general` and `workflow:continue` must run agent-registry validation before pipeline stages.

COMMIT_SLICE_CLASSIFICATION_RULE

- Source manifest:
  - `to-do/commit_slices.json`
- Required report command:
  - `npm run commit:slices:report -- --strict`
- Enforcement:
  1) every changed file must resolve to at least one slice (`unsliced_total = 0`)
  2) slice assignment precedence is manifest order (first match wins)
  3) multi-match files are allowed as informational (`multi_match_total`) but must include chosen primary slice in report
- Output report path:
  - `data/output/databases/polyglot-default/reports/commit_slice_report.json`

GLOBAL_FILE_UPDATE_LOG_RULE

- Source of truth:
  - `scripts/repo-update-log.js`
  - `source://update_events_file`
  - `source://update_sessions_file`
  - `source://update_state_file`
- Required behavior: log every file update event with timing metadata across application, agents, skills, rules, and scripts.
- Mandatory commands:
  - Baseline/closeout scan:
    - `npm run updates:scan -- --actor <agent-id> --scope "<scope>"`
  - Live event capture:
    - `npm run updates:watch -- --actor <agent-id> --session-id <session-id>`
- Any agent edit pass must run scan at start and end.
- Long-running edit/refactor passes must run watch mode while edits are in progress.

BLOCKING_GATE_RULES

- A pass is incomplete if any required check fails.
- No deferred cleanup is allowed.
- Required checks:
  - npm run lint --silent
  - npm test --silent
  - npm run refactor:gate --silent (or npm run refactor:gate)

NO_FIXER_PASS_RULE

- "Cleanup later" is disallowed for naming/literal/grouping/alignment issues.
- First pass must include:
  - naming compliance
  - pattern extraction
  - module/group/dispatch alignment
  - alias sync (if aliases changed)

JSON_SOURCE_OF_TRUTH_RULE

- Domain data in JS is forbidden when the same structure can be represented as JSON.
- Required extraction targets:
  - grouping maps
  - labeling maps
  - alias maps
  - operation/instruction registries
- Required storage location pattern:
  - `data/input/shared/<domain>/*.json`
- JS modules must consume JSON catalogs instead of embedding equivalent data walls.
- Required audit command:
  - `npm run audit:data-separation --`
- Latest report path:
  - `data/output/databases/polyglot-default/analysis/data_separation_audit_report.json`

BRAIN_DATA_TODO_LAYOUT_RULE

- Root architecture is:
  - `brain/` for functions and wrappers only
  - `data/input/` for inbound catalogs/datastream banks
  - `data/output/` for generated artifacts/logs/reports
  - `to-do/` for out-of-scope or staging assets
- Agents and skills are currently staged under:
  - `to-do/agents/`
  - `to-do/skills/`
- Any new runtime function must be placed under `brain/*`.
- Any new groups/labels/aliases catalog must be placed under `data/input/shared/*`.

SINGLE_WRAPPER_TWO_PASS_RULE

- Runtime orchestration must support one unified wrapper entrypoint.
- Wrapper source of truth:
  - `brain/wrappers/unified_io_wrapper.js`
- Wrapper catalog source of truth:
  - `data/input/shared/wrapper/unified_wrapper_specs.json`
- Mandatory pass order:
  1) `identify_arguments` (must succeed)
  2) `execute_pipeline`
- Pass 2 is blocked if pass 1 reports missing args.

INSTRUCTION_TEMPLATE_DEDUPE_RULE

- Repeated instruction sequences must be extracted into template registries.
- Operation definitions must reference template IDs (`instruction_template_refs`) when overlap exists.
- New operations cannot duplicate existing instruction blocks unless justified by non-overlapping behavior.

WRAPPER_ACTION_RULE

- Runtime wrappers must be 1:1 action runners.
- Business operations must execute via ordered instruction actions.
- Input requirements must be identified before execution (`identify_needed_data` contract).
- Avoid branch-heavy wrappers; prefer deterministic action maps and explicit inputs.

DISPATCH_FIRST_RENDERER_RULE

- Repeated forwarding wrappers in `app/renderer.js` are forbidden.
- Use grouped dispatch registries and object-path calls.
- Dispatch mapping source of truth:
  - data/input/shared/renderer/dispatch_specs.js
- Dispatch factory source:
  - brain/wrappers/renderer_dispatch_domain.js

BOOT_SPEC_SPLIT_RULE

- `renderer/boot/app_bootstrap.js` must be orchestration-only.
- Hook metadata/spec walls must be extracted by scope into `renderer/boot/specs/*`.
- Legacy module loading must be manifest-driven.

ALIGNMENT_RULE

If extracted-domain keys change, update all in the same pass:

1) PATTERN_EXTRACTED_MODULE (app/renderer.js)
2) GROUP_SETS module_key alignment (data/input/shared/renderer/group_sets.js)
3) DISPATCH_SPEC_MAP entries (data/input/shared/renderer/dispatch_specs.js)
4) Alias sources when aliases changed:
   - brain/modules/alias-index.js
   - data/input/shared/alias/alias_groups.js

NAMING_RULES

- Top registries/config maps: UPPER_SNAKE
- Reused literals/maps: PATTERN_*
- Runtime group aliases: G_APP, G_RT, G_PAGE, G_DOM, G_UNI, G_UNI_FX
- Dispatch maps: PATTERN_DISPATCH_*
- Linked ownership chain required for named entities: Window_Page_Control_Module

SIZE_GATES

- app/renderer.js <= 2400 lines
- renderer/boot/app_bootstrap.js <= 260 lines

VALIDATION_GATES

- Automated:
  - npm run lint --silent
  - npm test --silent
  - npm run refactor:gate --silent (or npm run refactor:gate)
- Runtime smoke checklist (required):
  - auth create/login/logout
  - tree selection/range/archive
  - sentence graph interactions
  - command palette open/filter/execute
  - universe render/benchmark/path/selection
  - logs window open/stream

ENFORCEMENT

- Any violation of blocking, alignment, naming, or size rules blocks pass completion.

AGENT_REVIEW_DECISION_FLOW

- Use reviewer/decider chain for agent-skill architecture changes:
  1) `agent-skill-review-research` creates comparison alternatives + decision packet.
  2) `agent-skill-decision-editor` applies final edits to `SKILL.md` and agent metadata.
- Reviewer output must include explicit file-level edit intents before decider edits begin.
